<p>This document provides a complete guide to training classification model=
s in GigaCheck. The classification task predicts document-level labels (hum=
an vs. AI-generated) for text samples using a Mistral-7B base model fine-tu=
ned with LoRA adapters and Deepspeed ZeRO-2 optimization.</p>
<p>This page covers the training workflow for classification models only. F=
or detection model training (character-level interval prediction), see <a h=
ref=3D"https://deepwiki.com/ai-forever/gigacheck/4.2-detection-model-traini=
ng" class=3D"text-neutral-300 hover:text-neutral-200 hover:underline">Detec=
tion Model Training</a>. For data preparation and format specifications, se=
e <a href=3D"https://deepwiki.com/ai-forever/gigacheck/3.1-data-format-spec=
ification" class=3D"text-neutral-300 hover:text-neutral-200 hover:underline=
">Data Format Specification</a> and <a href=3D"https://deepwiki.com/ai-fore=
ver/gigacheck/3.2-classification-dataset-loaders" class=3D"text-neutral-300=
 hover:text-neutral-200 hover:underline">Classification Dataset Loaders</a>=
. For detailed model architecture information, see <a href=3D"https://deepw=
iki.com/ai-forever/gigacheck/5.2-classification-head-and-lora" class=3D"tex=
t-neutral-300 hover:text-neutral-200 hover:underline">Classification Head a=
nd LoRA</a>.</p>
