</svg></button></h3>
<p>When <code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] te=
xt-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#48484=
8]/30">--lora_enable True</code> is specified, LoRA adapters are applied wi=
th:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Rank (<code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0=
.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before:hidden after:hidden dark:=
bg-[#484848]/30">--lora_r</code>)</strong>: <code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#=
e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before=
:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">8</code> - Defines the inner dim=
ension of the adapter matrices (A: d=E2=86=92r, B: r=E2=86=92d)</li>
<li><strong>Target modules</strong>: Query, key, value, output projections =
in attention layers, and gate/up/down projections in feed-forward layers</l=
i>
<li><strong>Trainable parameters</strong>: Only LoRA adapter weights and th=
e classification head are trained; base model weights remain frozen</li>
</ul>
<p>This reduces trainable parameters from ~7 billion to approximately 4-8 m=
illion, enabling:</p>
<ul>
<li>Faster training</li>
<li>Lower memory requirements</li>
<li>Reduced risk of catastrophic forgetting</li>
<li>Easier model versioning and distribution</li>
</ul>
